Release Notes_1001_
\layout Standard

Welcome to the new Mahogany release! If you haven't installed the program
 yet, you probably want to start by doing it.
 Please check if we don't have prebuilt binaries for your platform (currently
 we only provide binaries for Linux andWin32).
 If not, you'll have to build it from the sources: please refer to the README
 file for the compilation instructions.
 Mahogany should generally work on any modern Unix flavour but, of course,
 you can always contact us if you have any problems with building it.
\layout Subsection

Changes against the previous versions
\layout Subsubsection

0.64 against 0.63
\layout Standard

This time the most important changes have happened to the already existing
 features many of which were dramatically improved.
 Support for both IMAP4 andPOP3 has got better, many UI improvements were
 done and too many bugs to mention here were fixed.
\layout Standard

The main change without doubt is the complete reorganisation of the program
 internals which now allows us to only download the headers shown on the
 screen from server instead of getting all of them.
 This means that the time needed to open a folder is now almost independent
 of the folder size and Mahogany can be used without troubles with folders
 containing 50000 messages (and maybe more - but this wasn't tested yet).
\layout Standard

But what would be a new release without some new features? So here they
 are:
\layout Itemize

Added optional support for viewing and printing the HTML messages.
 Also added an optional text-only viewer and a viewer bar to quickly change
 the current viewer.
\layout Itemize

Added possibility to monitor a folder (or server) in the background just
 updading the number of messages in it but without actually downloading
 them.
\layout Itemize

IMAP server-side sorting and threading can now be used if available.
 It is also possible to sort and thread messages simultaneously.
 Both are now also done much more efficiently and more correctly.
\layout Itemize

Mahogany now remembers the flags for the POP3 servers and new mail detection
 for them works much more reliably which now makes Mahogany a much better
 POP3 client (provided your server supports UIDL POP command).
 POP3 code also tries to be faster by optionally using TOP instead of downloadin
g the entire messages.
\layout Itemize

Support for List-Post header and the possibility to configure the program
 to automatically reply to the mailing list only.
\layout Itemize

Added rename and copy buttons to the filter editing dialog.
\layout Itemize

Added "Open as readonly" command - this can be significantly faster than
 "Open" for the local folders and also works for the read only files.
\layout Itemize

Added a command to permanently delete messages instead of moving them to
 theTrash folder - useful for dealing with spam.
\layout Itemize

Filters were sped up even more.
 They also show a nicer progress dialog now.
\layout Itemize

Added commands to manually update the status of one or all folders.
\layout Itemize

Also added commands to mark messages as read or unread.
\layout Standard

Some of the notable UI improvements are:
\layout Itemize

Quoting the original text when replying is now optional, you can also choose
 to include only the text selected in the viewer in the reply.
\layout Itemize

Progress dialogs are shown while Mahogany is performing some long operations.
 The existing progress dialogs shown while retrieving the message headers
 now show the details of the messages being retrieved.
\layout Itemize

Password handling in case they are not stored in the config file has been
 improved - Mahogany can now remember them for this session only instead
 of keeping prompting for them.
\layout Itemize

Clicking on the header in the folder view window gives fast access to the
 sorting/threading menu with many useful items.
\layout Itemize

Scrolling beyond the end of the current messages (optionally) selects the
 next unread message or folder.
\layout Itemize

It is possible to rename the folder in the tree and the underlying folder
 file or mailbox independently of each other.
\layout Standard

The Win32 version has now some more of the possibilities of the Unix one:
\layout Itemize

SSL support is now available under Windows.
\layout Itemize

Mahogany can play a sound on receiving a new mail (optionally, of course).
\layout Subsubsection

0.63 against 0.62
\layout Standard

Again, most of the effort went into optimizing the program for speed.
 Filtering and moving mail messages on IMAP servers is now an order of magnitude
 faster and startup time has been reduced too (especially under Windows).
 Several fatal bugs which had unfortunately crept into Win32 release were
 fixed as well.
\layout Standard

The new features this time include
