Why not the GPL/BSD/QPL/my favourite license?
\layout Standard

Recently discussions about which license to chose for which project provoked
 major flamewars in the Unix community.
 There is a trend to put everything under the GPL or LGPL
\begin_float footnote 
\layout Standard

which we recently felt victim of - due to some strong demand, we have decided
 to allow alternatively licensing Mahogany under GPL
\end_float 
.
 We do not want to get involved in this highly emotional and political discussio
n.
 Our intent is to allow everyone to use and modify Mahogany while preserving
 some form of control over its development.
 That is why we chose a modified version of Perl's Artistic License.
 It is both more and less restrictive than the GPL in certain ways.
 We do not believe that there is one right license for everything.
 The Mahogany Artistic License is much simpler and easier to understand
 than the GPL, so we feel more comfortable with it.
 If you want to do something with Mahogany and feel that the license poses
 a problem, 
