User configuration files (Unix only)
\layout Standard

When run for the first time, 
\emph on 
Mahogany
\emph default 
 creates a directory called 
\family typewriter 
.M
\family default 
 in the user's home directory.
 The file 
\family typewriter 
$HOME/.M/config
\family default 
 will contain the current program configuration for this user.
 Only values different from the default configuration are stored here.
 If you want to obtain a list of all possible options (although arguably
 if you are so curious, you'd better read 
\emph on 
Mahogany
\emph default 
 sources directly), you can manually add the entry
\layout Quote


\family typewriter 
RecordDefaults = 1
\layout Standard

to the 
\family typewriter 
[M/Profiles]
\family default 
 section of the configuration file.
 This will cause all values which are used to be written to the configuration
 file.
\layout Standard

Note that an easy way to 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

reinstall
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 Mahogany is to move 
\family typewriter 
$HOME/.M/config 
\family default 
file to some other location or even delete it and restart Mahogany - then
 it will go through the installation process once again.
\layout Subsection

System wide configuration file
\layout Standard


\emph on 
Mahogany
\emph default 
 can be pre-configured on a system wide basis by supplying a 
\family typewriter 
M.conf
\family default 
 file in the installation directory (e.g.
 
\family typewriter 
/usr/share/Mahogany/M.conf
\family default 
).
 The syntax for this configuration file is identical to the user's configuration
 file, so you can just copy a user's file to this location and edit it by
