The quick and dirty approach: Create an addressbook entry and simply list
 multiple, comma separated, addresses in its Email field.
 Mahogany will use the whole contents of this field when expanding aliases.
 
\layout Itemize

The more elegant method: Create a new group in your addressbook and add
 the individual addresses as sub-entries of this group.
 If you use the group name as a mail alias, Mahogany will expand it to the
 list of email addresses of all of its group members.
 This is more powerful, as you can easily add and remove entries to sub
 groups.
