Can I run Mahogany as root?
\layout Standard


\shape italic 
Very simple question: can I run Mahogany on a unix system as the superuser
 (root)?
\layout Standard

Not directly.
 There are two problems with it:
\layout Enumerate

It is not a good idea for security reasons.
 In fact, you should not even run X11 as root.
 Though, we would not dare to impose that on you, if you want to, that is
 your problem.
\layout Enumerate

The technical reason, and this is why Mahogany does not allow it: The c-client
 library that we use for accessing mail folders and servers uses the user-Id
 0 (root) internally and does not work when called as root.
 When inquiring why this is so, c-client's author told us that it was bad
 to read mail as root - he thinks he knows what is good for you.
 Unless we find an easy way to circumvent that problem, you will not be
 able to run Mahogany as root as we have no time and desire to re-write
 the c-client library just for this.
\layout Standard

There is a workaround however:
\layout Standard

You can forward your email to another user, say 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 


\family typewriter 
user1
\family default 

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

, by creating a 
\family typewriter 
/root/.forward 
\family default 
file containing that user's name.
 Then, run Mahogany through the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 


\family typewriter 
su
\family default 

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 command: 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 


\family typewriter 
su user1 -c mahogany
\family default 

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

.
 This will work just fine.
 If you get an error message about it being unable to access your X11 display,
 do a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 


\family typewriter 
xhost localhost
\family default 

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 before, which will allow all local users to access your display.
 All this is not very safe from a security point of view if you don't trust
 your local machine, but perfectly fine for standalone or dialup boxes.
\layout Standard

Update: Mahogany now runs as "root".
